column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Approx 90% bridged ice cover at the constriction control adjacent to the gauge. Open leads downstream in the reach between the control adjacent to gauge and outflow to small intermediary pool near ~QUOTE~alternate wading section~QUOTE~ approx 30m downstream. Ice /depth conditions unsuitable for measurement at that section. Chipped out a thin transect of bridged ice adjacent to gauge for measurement - tried to minimize disruption to ice around control as much as possible while still obtaining a measurement.
column14: Measurement should be treated as estimate only. Looked for a long time for the best measurement section - ice conditions at alternate wading section 30m ds gauge precluded it from measurement. Possibility of section just ds of that where creek enters pool but significant + deep recirculating eddy - extrapolations would likely be highly unrepresentative of actual conditions.Adjacent to control considered best available -  thin transect bridged ice chipped away for measurement. Two measurements taken at almost the same section (second approx 1m ds)- tried to flip probe on second measurement to minimize boundary interference from triangular rock constriction. Measurements are not particularly comparable but both are at the very lower bounds of effective FlowTracker measurement. Both measurements have significant QA/QC concerns and should be treated as an estimate only. First considered slightly superior due to lower calculated uncertainty and slightly more even depth profile - this measurement imported into eHSN. Both measurements should be imported into Aquarius for comparison. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Old offset 28.572, reset @ 1159, new offset didn't apply to 1200 reading. New offset = 28.582. Used SL3 calibrate function - HG changed 0.003 between DWL and RS, reset is 0.003m off. Mid-section
HG: 29.146 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Reset (RS)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , Light Snow , Calm Wind
column13: Some bridged ice slightly upstream of control, definitely edge ice on control and downstream of control. Fairly extensive ice cover downstream of control. Extensive snow. Tried not to alter control while accessing gauge but some snow slumped in to the narrow control and caused a jam that was evident by sound and flow visually decreasing below control. Tried to clear it to match similar conditions to when we arrived prior to measurement.
column14: Measured at triangular section adjacent to gauge. Usual spot downstream was too shallow for effective FlowTracker 2 measurement. Unable to meet QAQC standards - this measurement should be treated as an estimate. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Old offset = 28.577999. Reset 1407MST. New offset = 28.572001. Not sure why so many sig figs in the offset but otherwise fine. Calculated MGH manually in Excel and added to eHSN using measurement mean time.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Very low water. Some leaves on control and downstream. Could possibly produce some degree of backwater at this low stage. Surveyed what is believed to be control/point of zero flow for rating development/verification.
column14: RFT NOTE; ADDED 0.0003 CMS TO ROUND UP TO 3 SIG FIGS (AS PER STANDARDS) Performed FT2 measurement approx 0.5m downstream of triangular channel constriction adjacent to gauge. Unable to complete 20 panels due to low water, only 1 good spot for measurement, but only 0.48m wide. Performed another estimate for corroboration at triangular section of channel, width = 0.48m, depth = 0.12m, single-shot velocity from FT2 = 0.0715m/s. Estimate = 0.48*0.12*0.0715*0.5 (due to triangular section) = 0.002cms. Mmnt = 0.0037cms. Defer to measurement, should probably be treated as an estimate only though. eHSN not loading curve information for some reason at this time. Can be viewed in Aquarius. Confirmed that the metal FT2 adapter fits nicely on the rod that is in the gauge and attaches snugly to FT2. No need to hike in the FT2 rod anymore - just the cylindrical adapter. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Old offset = 28.732. RS@1231 28.751. Block in just over 30cm water (calculated 0.37m), reset block, moved further out. New OD 0.544m @1253MST. Reset 1311MST. New offset = 28.578m.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Lake CIC, except thin ice/open near outlet. Minimal edge ice on control and within sight downstream. More ice cover noted approx 100-200m downstream (COL5 picture). Pictures taken.
column14: Flowtracker 2 measurement approx 20m downstream of gauge/control before larger pool. Marked alternate wading section on station description. Fair/good measurement. Fair uncertainty 4.9%. eHSN shows 9.86%, unsure how that number is calculated. Some angles, particularly near right bank as expected, but angles consistent throughout. Relatively smooth/even depth profile. Not bad for this station. Old offset = 28.723. RS@1446MST. New offset = 28.732.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind Swirling/Variable
column14: Measurement approx. 20-30m downstream of gauge, just upstream of larger pool. Best available measurement section and measurement, with large flow angles and concentrated flow on right hand side unavoidable at this station, particularly at lower stage. At site this seemed to be one of the better FT2 measurements completed in recent memory, but on review at office uncertainty is high and measurement quality pretty average for this station, poor or fair at best.  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of 0.008 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 29.197 No reset due to 0.005 lake surge. Leave stilling bucket at gauge over winter. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy , Light Rain , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: High velocity, turbulent water at control.
column14: Unable to measure at usual section without flipping ADCP small boat due to high velocity and turbulence. Measured 129m ESE (heading 105T) downstream below control. New section seems good with lamniar flow, slower but acceptable velocities, well defined between large boulders. After measurement was completed, very slow flow was observed adjacant to creek in a marshy area on left bank. Unable to find the source or confluence of flow with creek, did not seem to be connected to creek, possible groundwater seepage or very small amounts of flow from creek under large rocks a few meters upstream. Discharge through the marshy area likely very small percentage of creek flow, probably negligible, but may explain if this measurement turns out to be an outlier. Pictures taken. This still seems to be the best section and measurement we could obtain today given equipment and conditions at site. Attempts to measure at the usual section at this stage may require larger trimirand. Right edge modified in WR2 post processing to account for very small distance to edge when closely inspected during the measurement, resulting in change of 0.01cms (<1%) discharge.  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of 0.005 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 29.591 Shot from BM86-2 due to high water, unable to set up on right side of creek. Started benchmark tie, not completed due to unideal setup for BM tie as could not set up on right bank due to high water, time constraint prevented further attempts. Tied in 86-1 only. WL taken on right side of creek as close to sensor as possible, near BM83-500. MGH retrieved from telemetry. ADCP by Moving Boat
